Fixed-P residual: extend L at fixed P (g=delta=P/L). Larger L = smaller g =
smaller per-turn resource step. If alpha* CONVERGES -> residual is discretization
(numerical, vanishes in continuum limit). If it keeps moving -> a real 2nd group.

P = 1.0
    L      g=d   alpha*  decrement
    5  0.20000    2.650           
   10  0.10000    2.800     +0.150
   20  0.05000    2.550     -0.250
   40  0.02500    1.950     -0.600
   80  0.01250    1.450     -0.500
  160  0.00625    1.200     -0.250

P = 0.5
    L      g=d   alpha*  decrement
    5  0.10000    1.450           
   10  0.05000    1.250     -0.200
   20  0.02500    1.050     -0.200
   40  0.01250    1.000     -0.050
   80  0.00625    1.000     +0.000
  160  0.00313    1.000     +0.000

